connectivity_enlighten.description: Whether connectivity to Enlighten could be established. This is only available when performing a network connectivity check.

connectivity_enphase.description: Whether connectivity to Enphase could be established. This is only available when performing a network connectivity check.

..destination: The destination of the route in the network routing table. This is only available when getting the network routing table data.
..dhcp: Whether or not DHCP is allowed to dynamically configure this interface.

enlighten_dns_lookup.description: Whether a DNS lookup for Enlighten could be performed. This is only available when performing a network connectivity check.

enphase_dns_lookup.description: Whether a DNS lookup for Enphase could be performed. This is only available when performing a network connectivity check.

..entry: The order of the route in the network routing table. This is only available when getting the network routing table data.
..flags: The flags for the route in the network routing table. This is only available when getting the network routing table data.
..gateway: The default gateway for this interface, or if as part of the network routing table data, the gateway for this route.
..gateway_ping: The response time (or `fail`) of an ICMP ping of the default gateway. This is only available when performing a network connectivity check.
..genmask: The generality (i.e. the netmask) of the route in the network routing table. This is only available when getting the network routing table data.

google_dns_lookup.description: Whether a DNS lookup for Google(R) could be performed. This is only available when performing a network connectivity check.

..google_ping: The response time (or `fail`) of an ICMP ping of the Google server. This is only available when performing a network connectivity check.
..iface: The interface for the route in the network routing table. This is only available when getting the network routing table data.
..ip: The IP address of the interface.
..metric: The metric for the route in the network routing table. This is only available when getting the network routing table data.
..pingip: The IP address that was ICMP pinged.
..primary_dns: The primary DNS server for this interface.
..primary_dns_ping: The response time (or `fail`) of an ICMP ping of the primary DNS server. This is only available when performing a network connectivity check.
..primary_interface: The interface primarily used for network connectivity. This is only available when performing a network connectivity check.
..ref: The number of references for the route in the network routing table, such as how many other routes (e.g. through gateways) rely on the presence of this route. This is only available when getting the network routing table data.
..results: The results of an ICMP ping.
..secondary_dns: The secondary DNS server for this interface.
..secondary_dns_ping: The response time (or `fail`) of an ICMP ping of the secondary DNS server. This is only available when performing a network connectivity check.
..use: The number of times the routing entry has been used for the route in the network routing table. This is only available when getting the network routing table data.

consumption.description: An object that contains the consumption details for the request.

production.description: An object that contains the production details for the request.

storage.description: An object that contains the storage details for the request.

activeCount.description: How many of these devices are active.

Device.apprntPwr: The apparent power value. The combination of reactive and true power measurement in Volt-Amperes (VA). Only available with the `eim` device type.

lines.description: Provides a further breakdown for each of the phases. Only available if the querystring `details` is set to true in the request and with the `eim` device type.

measurementType.description: What type of measurement this is reporting. Only available with the `eim` device type.

Device.pwrFactor: The power factor value. The ratio of the real power absorbed by the load to the apparent power flowing in the circuit. Only available with the `eim` device type.
Device.reactPwr: The reactive power value. The dissipated power resulting from inductive and capacitive loads measured in Volt-Amperes reactive (var). Only available with the `eim` device type.
Device.readingTime: The date and time in epoch format that the measurement was taken.
Device.rmsCurrent: The Root Mean Square current value. Only available with the `eim` device type.
Device.rmsVoltage: The Root Mean Square voltage value. Only available with the `eim` device type.

state.description: The state the AC Battery device is currently in. Only available with the `acb` device type.

type.description: Specifies what type of device this is a response from.

Device.vahLifetime: The total Volt-Ampere hour this device has seen. Only available with the `eim` device type.
Device.vahToday: The total number of Volt-Ampere hours (vah) seen today. Only available with the `eim` device type.
Device.varhLagLifetime: The total lagging Volt-Ampere reactive hours (varh) this device has seen. Only available with the `eim` device type.
Device.varhLagToday: The total lagging Volt-Ampere reactive hours (varh) seen today. Only available with the `eim` device type.
Device.varhLeadLifetime: The total leading Volt-Ampere reactive hours (varh) this device has seen. Only available with the `eim` device type.
Device.varhLeadToday: The total leading Volt-Ampere reactive hours (varh) seen today. Only available with the `eim` device type.
Device.whLastSevenDays: The total number of watt-hours seen in the last 7 days. Only available with the `eim` device type.
Device.whLifetime: The total number of watt-hours (Wh) this device has seen.
Device.whNow: Unknown. Only available with the `acb` device type.
Device.whToday: The total number of watt-hours seen today. Only available with the `eim` device type.
Device.wNow: The number of watts currently being reported.

Lines.apprntPwr: The apparent power value on this phase. The combination of reactive and true power measurement in Volt-Amperes (VA).
Lines.pwrFactor: The power factor value on this phase. The ratio of the real power absorbed by the load to the apparent power flowing in the circuit.
Lines.reactPwr: The reactive power value on this phase. The dissipated power resulting from inductive and capacitive loads measured in Volt-Amperes Reactive (VAR).
Lines.rmsCurrent: The Root Mean Square current value in Amps on this phase.
Lines.rmsVoltage: The Root Mean Square voltage value in Vrms on this phase.
Lines.vahLifetime: The total Volt-Ampere hour (vah) this device has seen on this phase.
Lines.vahToday: The total number of Volt-Ampere hours (vah) seen today on this phase.
Lines.varhLagLifetime: The total lagging Volt-Ampere reactive hour (varh) this device has seen on this phase.
Lines.varhLagToday: The total lagging Volt-Ampere reactive hours (varh) seen today on this phase.
Lines.varhLeadLifetime: The total leading Volt-Ampere reactive hour (varh) this device has seen on this phase.
Lines.varhLeadToday: The total leading Volt-Ampere reactive hours (varh) seen today on this phase.
Lines.whLastSevenDays: The total number of watt-hours seen on this phase in the last 7 days.
Lines.whLifetime: The total number of watts this device has seen on this phase.
Lines.whToday: The total number of watt-hours seen today on this phase.
Lines.wNow: The number of watts currently being reported on this phase.

..dont_retry_failed_files: If an update fails whether it should be retried.
..force: Whether the update should be applied even if the device would not usually apply it due to a pre-condition failing (e.g. off-grid, low-SoC etc).
..overwrite_low_soc: Whether the update should apply even if the battery has a low State of Charge (SoC).
..overwrite_off_grid: Whether the update should apply even if the system is currently off-grid.

..commission_only: Whether to apply to only commissioned devices.
..Offgrid-Check: Whether the command will be applied even if off-grid.
..SOC-check: Whether the command will be applied even if the batteries are a low State of Charge (SoC).

Connection.sc_debug: Whether data is being written to the debug stream.

Counters.main_CfgChanged: The number of times the configuration has been changed.
Counters.main_CfgLoad: The number of times the configuration has been loaded.

Counters.MqttClient_setCallbacks: The number of times the callback has been set on the MQTT to process messages.
Counters.MqttClient_subscribe: The number of times the MQTT client has subscribed to a topic.
Counters.rest_Status: The number of API REST calls the Gateway has handled.
Counters.sc_hdlDataPub: The number of times the hardware description language (HDL) has been published?
Counters.sc_SendStreamCtrl: The number of times the send stream functionality has been controlled.
Counters.SSL_Keys_Create: The number of Secure Socket Layer (SSL) or Transport Layer Security (TLS) keys that have been created.

Tasks.timestamp: The unix epoch timestamp of the last task processed.

description.long: A HTTP GET to `/stream/meter` can be used to get 21 - 23 "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Server-sent_events[Server-Sent Events (SSE)]" (MIME type `text/event-stream`) formatted objects of the meter data every 21 - 23 seconds. This is presumably due to the Gateway polling every second but buffering the data (potentially a 16 KB = 16384 byte buffer?). This can be consumed by the `EventSource` JavaScript API.
description.short: Obtain a continuous stream of meter readings.

net-consumption.description: An object that contains the consumption meter readings for systems with solar production included.

production.description: An object that contains the production meter readings.

total-consumption.description: An object that contains the consumption meter readings for systems measuring the load only.

Phase.f: The frequency of the system (e.g. 50 Hz in the UK).
Phase.i: The Root Mean Square current value in Amps (elsewhere called `rmsCurrent`).
Phase.p: The number of watts currently being reported (elsewhere called `wNow`).
Phase.pf: The power factor value. The ratio of the real power absorbed by the load to the apparent power flowing in the circuit (elsewhere called `pwrFactor`).
Phase.q: The reactive power value. The dissipated power resulting from inductive and capacitive loads measured in Volt-Amperes reactive (var) (elsewhere called `reactPwr`).
Phase.s: The apparent power value. The combination of reactive and true power measurement in Volt-Amperes (VA) (elsewhere called `apprntPwr`).
Phase.v: The Root Mean Square voltage value in Vrms (elsewhere called `rmsVoltage`).

description.short: Obtain a continuous stream of Power-Spectral-Density analysis of the Power-Line Communication (PLC).

Stream - Power Spectral Density (PSD).name: Power Spectral Density (PSD)
Stream - Power Spectral Density (PSD).notes: Idle data is returned if no extra data is provided in the body of the request two types of server-sent events are sent: 1. "config" event type: the data is JSON, e.g. {"plc": {"f": 103, "bw": 20}} where f is PLC frequency and bw is PLC bandwidth, both in kHz. 2. "message" (default) event type: the data is semicolon delimited pairs of (t,v) where t is in microseconds and v is in arbitrary units.
